11 An Act relating to schools; amending 70 O.S. 2021,
Sections 6-149.7 and 24-101.3, which relate to
12 student suspensions; subjecting certain students in
grades three through five to school suspensions;
13 allowing modification of certain suspension terms;
mandating certain suspension and expulsion protocols
14 for certain offenses; updating reference; providing
an effective date; and declaring an emergency.
15
16
17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
18 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 6-149.7, is
19 amended to read as follows:
20 Section 6-149.7. A. No student enrolled in a school shall
21 assault, attempt to cause physical bodily injury, or act in a manner
22 that could reasonably cause bodily injury to an education employee
23 or a person who is volunteering for the school. Any student in
24 grades three through five who violates the provisions of this
HB3885 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

CORRECTED
1 sect ion shall be subject to suspension as provided for in Section
2 24-101.3 of this title. Such term of suspension may be modified by
3 the district superintendent on a case-by-case basis. Any student in
4 grades six through twelve who violates the provisions of this
5 section shall be subject to out-of-school suspension as provided for
6 in Section 24-101.3 of this title. This section shall be in
7 addition to and does not limit the criminal liability of a person
8 who causes or commits an assault, battery, or assault and battery
9 upon a school employee as provided for in Section 650.7 of Title 21
10 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
11 B. No education employee shall be liable for the use of
12 necessary and reasonable force to control and discipline a student
13 during the time the student is in attendance at the school or in
14 transit to or from the school, or any other function authorized by
15 the school district.
16 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 24-101.3, is
17 amended to read as follows:
18 Section 24-101.3. A. Any student who is guilty of an act
19 described in paragraph 1 of subsection C of this section may be
20 suspended out-of-school in accordance with the provisions of this
21 section. Each school district board of education shall adopt a
22 policy with procedures which provides for out-of-school suspension
23 of students. The policy shall address the term of the out-of-school
24 suspension, provide an appeals process as described in subsection B
